<TITLE> Aktel fined Tk 145 crore for VoIP business </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission has fined mobile phone service provider Aktel Tk 145 crore for dodging revenues by transferring phone calls abroad using VoIP, BTRC said Sunday. Law enforcers and BTRC officials launched a joint operation against the "illegal" use of Voice over Internet Protocol technology after the caretaker government came to power. Investigations revealed that Aktel was involved in the "illegal" business, BTRC said, adding it seized the VoIP equipment and fined the company for dodging government revenues. BTRC chairman Manzurul Alam said he hoped that telecommunications companies would not use VoIP in future. He expected companies to cooperate with the government but vowed not to spare offenders. bdnews24.com
